cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.GR, cs.NA 

The paper deals with digital multichannel imaging applications, particularly color image filtering and enhancement, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces techniques to speed up vector filters using the minimax approximation theory, which falls under the mathematical optimization (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also involves experiments on a large and diverse set of color images, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with computational speed, which falls under the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
